// =====================================================================
//  test_bitmask_graph.hexa -- ROI #60 BFS/DFS -> bitmask optimization
//
//  Verifies bitmask-based graph traversal produces identical results
//  to array-based visited set, for small graphs (<=64 nodes).
//
//  Tests (27):
//    1.  BFS on 4-node graph (array)
//    2.  BFS on 4-node graph (bitmask)
//    3.  DFS on 4-node graph (array)
//    4.  DFS on 4-node graph (bitmask)
//    5.  BFS on disconnected graph
//    6.  DFS cycle detection
//    7.  BFS/DFS single node
//    8.  BFS linear chain
//    9.  DFS linear chain
//   10.  BFS on complete graph K4
//   11.  DFS on star graph
//   12.  BFS shortest path distance
//   13.  DFS back edge detection
//   14.  Bitmask bit() helper
//   15.  Bitmask bitor() helper
//   16.  Bitmask set/test
//   17.  Bitmask clear via XOR
//   18.  Bitmask popcount
//   19.  Bitmask union + intersection
//   20.  BFS on 8-node tree
//   21.  DFS on 8-node tree
//   22.  BFS bitmask popcount check
//   23.  DFS bitmask popcount check
//   24.  Bitmask boundary (bit 0 and bit 30)
//   25.  Connected components via bitmask BFS
//   26.  BFS level ordering
//   27.  Bitmask XOR (symmetric difference)
//
//  Run: ./hexa self/test_bitmask_graph.hexa
